ACTIONS
=======

 * "activate-transfer"
   Description: default action when tapping a transfer menuitem.
   If the transfer completed, clicking opens the destination application
   (eg, tapping on a listitem to view a picture in the Gallery).
   If the transfer failed or is paused, activation tries again.
   State: None
   Parameter: s an opaque uid to specify which transer to use.
                This uid comes from the menuitems' x-canonical-uid property.

 * "cancel-transfer"
 * "pause-transfer"
 * "resume-transfer"
   Description: actions that operate on a single transfer.
   State: None
   Parameter: s an opaque uid to specify which transer to use.
                This uid comes from the menuitems' x-canonical-uid property.

 * "pause-all"
 * "resume-all"
 * "clear-all"
   Description: actions that operate on all transfers.
   State: None
   Parameter: None

 * "transfer-states"
   Description: The transfers' mutable information; e.g. state and progress
   State: Dictionary containing key/value pairs of transfer uids strings to
          a per-transfer dictionary.
          The inner, per-transfer dictionaries will have key/value pairs for
           * "last-activity"  x the date of the last transfer activity
           * "percent"        d perent of the progress copmlete, [0.0 ... 1.0]
           * "state"          i int value matching the Transfer::State enum
   Parameter: none. invoking this action has no effect.


CUSTOM MENUITEMS
================

 * Transfer
   - x-canonical-type         s "com.canonical.indicator.transfer"
   - x-canonical-uid          s the transfer's unique identifier string
   - icon                     v the icon for the app receiving the download
   - label                    s human-readable string describing the transfer

